{
    "name": "Charlatan",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Charlatan",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Charlatans use pretense and misdirection to swindle money and other valuables from the credulous and confused. Selling snake oil (literally or figuratively), distracting marks to pick their pockets, or faking mediumship are classic grifts.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 18",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 209",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 209",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 209
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Criminals",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Criminal Scams",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Common scams criminals run include sending fake collectors for nonexistent charities to seek donations for the diseased and downtrodden; rigged games of chance at local fairs offering worthless prizes, and flashy sideshows concealing the work of pickpockets in the audience; and plants who offer to help travelers find accommodations but lead them to inns with exorbitant prices.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Fantasy Crimes",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "While many crimes in <i>Pathfinder</i> are similar to crimes in the real world, certain crimes are possible only in a world of magic. These include using magic to win a wager, malicious uses of <a aonid=\"38\" game-obj=\"Traits\">curses</a>, violating autonomy with <a aonid=\"61\" game-obj=\"Traits\">enchantment</a> magic, falsifying <a aonid=\"47\" game-obj=\"Traits\">divinations</a>, violating privacy with divinations, or trespassing via <a aonid=\"156\" game-obj=\"Traits\">teleportation</a>.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "More Scams",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "<ul><li>Fraudsters sell fake alchemical items, medicines, charms, talismans, or other minor magics.</li><li>Unscrupulous moneylenders take advantage of lax business regulations to employ predatory repayment terms.</li><li>Phony fortune-tellers and mediums use cold-reading techniques to lull gullible marks.</li></ul>",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Protection Money",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Criminal organizations often find it easier to demand protection money from locals than go to the trouble of stealing it. \u201cProtection\u201d includes an implicit assumption that those who pay up are safe from those criminals, and some also promise retribution against other criminals.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "Some criminals are the desperate who have no option but to break the law to survive, while others choose a life of crime for thrills, forming gangs or underworld guilds that specialize in certain illegal ventures.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 208
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
